TITLE: Rain, Wind Slow Otherwise Smooth Thanksgiving Travel
SUMMARY: TSA projects that more than 2.5 million people could pass through U.S. airports Sunday.

SUMMARY: Before returning to Venezuela, Chevron must collect debt, repair equipment and bolster its workforce.

SUMMARY: The oil giant shares a chunk of New Mexico land with mining companies, which makes drilling there a challenge.

SUMMARY: Blackouts have gotten longer and prices keep rising. Defenders say the company inherited a disaster after years of mismanagement and neglect.

SUMMARY: Lawmakers and farm groups are pushing to pass an immigrant-labor overhaul through both chambers of Congress before the GOP takes control of the House next year.

SUMMARY: Stores on average welcomed more consumers compared with last year, industry data show.

SUMMARY: Vlad, Niki, Diana and Nastya party on yachts, ride in Ferraris and travel the world. Their massive audience of fellow kids can’t get enough.
